answers.body_markdown:
This:

    int pixels[numeroPixeles];

is a *stack overflow* unless `numeroPixeles` is bounded by a small constant. Allocating large objects on the stack admits no way to distinguish success/failure; your program just blows up (and possibly yields code execution under the control of whoever authored the data you&#39;re processing). To work with arbitrary-size data like this you need `malloc` where you can check for success.

