I have managed to achieve your desired sorting with the following;

    db.collection.aggregate([
      {
        $lookup: {
          from: &quot;collection&quot;,
          localField: &quot;parentId&quot;,
          foreignField: &quot;_id&quot;,
          as: &quot;parent&quot;
        }
      },
      {
        $addFields: {
          fake_ts: {
            $cond: {
              if: { $eq: [ { $size: &quot;$parent&quot; }, 1 ] },
              then: &quot;$parent.ts&quot;,
              else: &quot;$ts&quot;
            }
          }
        }
      },
      {
        $sort: { 
          fake_ts: 1,
          ts: 1
        }
      },
      {
        $project: {
          fake_ts: 0,
          parent: 0
        }
      }
    ])

Where I first [join][1] with itself to get parent within each child document, then I [create a dummy field][2] (idea from @mickl), and use parent&#39;s `ts` for child documents. Then I just [`$sort`][3] &amp; [`$project`][4] out temp fields.

Sorting is done with first `fake_ts`, then with `ts`, so that we will get the child documents always under the parent, but they will be sorted with their own `ts` between themselves.

